26 May 2017Today, Friday, 26 May at 10h00, the Minister of Communications, Ms Ayanda Dlodlo and Deputy Minister Tandi Mahambehlala will table the Department of Communication Budget Vote for the 2017/18 financial year in the National Assembly.The objective of the DoC Budget Vote speech is to demonstrate to the Communication Portfolio Committee members and South African citizens how the departmental budget will be utilised to support annual strategic targets to ensure that the department delivers on its mandate. The Minister will report back on the activities and the work done by the two department and entities in the past financial year.Enquiries: Phumla Williams Cell: 083 501 0139Issued by Government Communication and Information System